                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d808">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bowen</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1902</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Bowen reports that he has been authorized by the Venezuelan Government to
                    cable to the British and German consuls that they may return from Curacao to La
                    Guaira.</p>
                <p>Italy has presented a note which Venezuela interprets as similar to the British
                    and German notes.</p>
                <p>The minister for foreign affairs has just informed Mr. Bowen that President
                    Castro and his wife are going this afternoon to call on the German minister’s
                    wife.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
